## Phase 3: Layout & Control Design Audit

### 3a. Control Sizing
```bash
# Find suspiciously small touch targets
grep -n "\.Size = new.*([0-9]\+, [0-9]\+)" **/*.Designer.cs 2>/dev/null | awk -F'[(),]' '{if ($3+0 < 24 || $4+0 < 24) print NR": "$0}' | head -20
```

**Flag:**
- Buttons smaller than 24×24px (should be at minimum 75×23 for standard buttons)
- Labels with fixed width that will truncate on different font sizes
- TextBoxes with width not anchored/docked — will not resize with window

### 3b. Anchoring & Docking
```bash
grep -n "\.Anchor\|\.Dock" **/*.Designer.cs 2>/dev/null | head -30
```

**Flag:**
- Controls with no Anchor and no Dock in a resizable form (they won't move when form resizes)
- Controls anchored to wrong edges for their purpose (e.g., status label not anchored Bottom)
- Mixing absolute layout with anchored controls in the same container

### 3c. Tab Order
```bash
grep -n "\.TabIndex\|\.TabStop" **/*.Designer.cs 2>/dev/null | head -30
```

**Flag:**
- TabIndex values that don't follow logical reading order (left-right, top-bottom)
- Interactive controls with `TabStop = false` without justification
- Missing tab index on new controls (gets default 0, disrupts existing order)

