## Phase 4: Accessibility Audit

```bash
# Check for missing accessibility text
grep -n "\.AccessibleName\|\.AccessibleDescription\|\.AccessibleRole" **/*.Designer.cs 2>/dev/null | head -20

# Check for controls that need accessible names but don't have them
grep -n "new System.Windows.Forms.Button\|new System.Windows.Forms.PictureBox" **/*.Designer.cs 2>/dev/null | head -20
```

**Flag:**
- Buttons, PictureBoxes, or custom controls with no `AccessibleName` set
- Labels used as group headers without `AccessibleRole = StaticText`
- Error indicators (colored panels, icons) with no accessible text equivalent
- ToolTip text missing on icon-only buttons

